name: Oregon Geospatial Enterprise Office, Urban Growth Boundaries, Oregon, 2007
description:
Urban Growth Boundaries polygons for Oregon Municipalities/Cities.
Purpose:
These data are intended for science researchers, students, policy makers, and the general public.
Urban Growth Boundaries were established by DLCD Statewide Planning Goal 14 defined in
OAR 660-015-000(14). This requires all cities to estimate future growth and plan/zone lands to
meet those needs. By law, the municipality is responsible for developing plans that implement the
Statewide Land Use Planning Goals. The areas include UGB amendments. UGBs were
defined/created as part of Goal 14 by the DLCD on 12/27/74.

author.source: OR Dept of Transportation (ODOT), OR Employment Dept, OGDC, Dept of Land Conservation and Development, Oregon Geospatial Enterprise Office
